text: Adnagulovo () is a rural locality (a selo) in Tatar-Ulkanovsky Selsoviet, Tuymazinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 258 as of 2010. There are 4 streets. == Geography == It is located 16 km from Tuymazy, 4 km from Tatar-Ulkanovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Tuymazinsky District
title: Adnagulovo
